This contributing file was created on 2024-01-26.

Welcome to U.S. Energy Information Administration’s (EIA) Contributing Guide.  Thank you for investing your time to our projects! Please read our Code of Conduct, https://github.com/EIAgov/EIAgov/blob/main/CODE%20OF%20CONDUCT, which we hold very important to create a positive environment for contributors.  

To get an overview of and individual project, please see the README.MD file for an individual respository.

Do you have an issue/Did you find a bug?
Please direct issues or bugs to <EIA-Project Name@eia.gov>. The <EIA Project Name> Team will communicate all issues or bugs (status/resolution) via an ISSUES doc within each respository.

If you are unable to find an open issue addressing the problem or bug, please open a new one by emailing <EIA-Project Name@eia.gov>. Be sure to include a title and clear description, with as much relevant information as possible, and a code sample or an executable test case demonstrating the expected behavior that is not occurring.

Do you intend to propose a new feature or change an existing one?
Suggest your change by sending an email to <EIA-Project Name@eia.gov>.

Do you have questions/concerns about the source code?
Ask any question or express any concerns about a project to <EIA Project Name> via <EIA-Project Name@eia.gov>.
